Identity & Entity Nexus (IDN)
1. Purpose of This Document
This document defines the versioning and evolution model for the Identity & Entity Nexus (IDN).
IDN versioning ensures that:
identity truth is stable and interpretable over time
historical identity states are never rewritten
merges, splits, and relationship changes are explainable
downstream engines can safely reason about identity provenance
2. Versioning Principles
Identity History Is Immutable
Once an identity state or event is recorded, it is never altered or deleted.
Evolution via Events
Changes occur through versioned events, not record mutation.
Temporal Truth
Identity meaning is time-aware; "current" is a projection, not a rewrite.
Deterministic Replay
Replaying the same events yields the same identity graph.
Forward Interpretability
Historical identity states remain readable as schemas evolve.
3. Versioned Components in IDN
The following components are versioned:
